Le cluster se donne pour objectifs de : 
-	Animer les acteurs du domaine de l’industrie ferroviaire (entreprises, centres de recherche et développement, établissements d’enseignement supérieur) autour de projets collaboratifs à fort contenu innovant dans les niches d’excellence identifiées ;
-	Créer un environnement technologique et des synergies favorables au développement de projets de R&D et d’innovation et à l’émergence de Start-up innovantes dans l’industrie ferroviaire ; 
-	Contribuer, par la mise en œuvre d’une démarche de veille et de prospective dédiée à l’industrie ferroviaire, à la réflexion stratégique et définition des objectifs opérationnels clairs partagés par l’ensemble de la communauté des acteurs publics et des entreprises ; 
-	Favoriser une dynamique de progrès permettant aux entreprises du cluster de devenir plus compétitives, se développer et conquérir des marchés à l’international ;
-	Offrir et développer toutes activités de services de soutien, de conseil et d’accompagnement des porteurs de projets ; 
-	Développer une politique de communication et de promotion du Cluster au plan national et international ; 
-	Organiser ou participer à l’organisation, tant au Maroc qu’à l’étranger, des manifestations à caractères commercial, promotionnel, industriel, ou technique, de nature à développer l’image du cluster, et à promouvoir les produits et services de ses entreprises membres.

Chi siamo
Il Centro di Formazione Ferroviaria srl è un Centro di Formazione riconosciuto dall’Agenzia Nazionale per la Sicurezza delle Ferrovie (secondo il Decreto Legislativo 10 agosto 2007 n.162), che si occupa di erogare corsi di formazione per personale impiegato in attività di sicurezza ferroviaria, in particolare per:
•	Condotta dei treni
•	Accompagnamento dei treni
•	Preparazione dei treni
•	Manutenzione veicoli
La società è stata fondata nel 2017 dall’unione di esperti in vari settori, con lo scopo di contribuire al miglioramento della formazione ferroviaria attuale e diventare uno dei principali poli di formazione della penisola.

Mission
La nostra mission è orientata al cliente, soprattutto verso privati che vogliono intraprendere la loro carriera nel settore ferroviario, e imprese che necessitano di formazione e servizi di consulenza in ambito ferroviario.
Perché scegliere noi?
•	la nostra formazione aumenterà le tue possibilità di essere assunto in una delle principali imprese ferroviarie italiane;
•	il nostro personale, formato da docenti accreditati di comprovata esperienza e professionalità,  ti accompagnerà nell’apprendimento e nello sviluppo delle tue competenze;
•	ampia offerta formativa con corsi organizzati tutto l’anno e in tutta Italia;
•	maggiore qualità della formazione grazie a classi poco numerose (max 15 studenti);
•	siamo l’unico Centro di Formazione in Italia ad avere a disposizione un simulatore di guida per la condotta dei treni;
•	il nostro team di professionisti sarà sempre a disposizione e pronto ad aiutarti in tutte le fasi del percorso.

Kilborn Consulting Limited is an independent railway engineering consultancy and design business.  We specialise in the design of new and altered railway Signalling and Telecoms systems for the UK railway infrastructure.

Kilborn Consulting Limited was formed in June 2000. Since that time, Kilborn Consulting Limited has grown to its current size, with 10 full and part time staff providing technical and administrative support to the Managing Director.

There are seven defined areas for which we supply our services:

Signalling and Telecoms Consultancy, including technical advice and support;
Asset Condition Assessments, Correlation and Surveys;
Signalling & Level Crossing Risk Assessments;
Feasibility, Optioneering studies, Concept and Outline Signalling Design;
Telecoms Option Selection Reports (including AiP), Reference System Design and Detailed Design;
Detailed Signalling Design;  and
Competency Management & Assessments.

We are approved as suppliers to the Railway Group through Achilles RISQS Audit.

New for 2019, RailWorx will give visitors the chance to see railway civil and systems engineering live and working.

RailWorx features will include:

The Drone Zone – they are increasingly in use over the railway, but what can they do?
Network Rail’s dedicated 'InnovationWorx' area showing the latest developments by the Signalling Innovation Group and in the fields of electrification and telecommunications;
The major civil engineering contractors, front line suppliers to Network Rail and HS2, looking to connect with their existing and potential supply chains;
Live demonstrations of machinery and plant used for railway civil engineering, including piling, reinforcing, drainage, access, lifting, surveying and monitoring;
'Consultants Row' where the industry’s designers and consultants show what they can do;
The Get SET Zone is designed to help visitors explore employment opportunities and to give them access to services they may need to get a new job, get back into work, or get their first job.

La nostra azienda nasce nel 1986 nel Segnalamento Ferroviario e soprattutto nella specializzazione nel cablaggio e posa di tutte le parti che compongono un Impianto A.C.E.I.

Nel corso degli anni cambiando le tipologie del segnalamento si adegua ai vari sistemi, attualmente in uso e più diffusi nella rete FS.
Attualmente il Segnalamento ferroviario è il settore prevalente della nostra attività, ma nel tempo abbiamo ampliato i nostri servizi aggiungendo i sottolencati prodotti.

Sono di nostra produzione:
Portoni blindati personalizzati, con pannelli in legno di massello, multistrato marino, laccati idrorepellenti, anche con vetri camera blindati e decorati;

Inferriate di sicurezza in ferro, con trattamento di zincatura a caldo, primer e verniciatura a polvere;

Persiane di sicurezza in ferro, con trattamento di zincatura a caldo, primer e verniciatura a polvere;

Combinate di sicurezza in ferro, (persiane e inferriate), con trattamento di zincatura a caldo, primer e verniciatura a polvere;

Cancelli e ringhiere in ferro.

Lavorazioni di lamiere in acciaio e in alluminio con macchine piegatrici e punzonatrici (pressopiegate e forate).

Commercializziamo:
Finestre in Legno-Alluminio, PVC e PVC-Legno**, porte in legno, porte in laminato, porte in cristallo, zanzariere, avvolgibili, tende da sole, pergotende, gazebi.

**(con certificazione per risparmio energetico e relativo incentivo fiscale. Sopralluogo e montaggio incluso)

The AB4Rail (Alternative Bearers for Rail) project was selected for funding within the framework of the European Horizon and the Shift2Rail Programs. The Radiolabs Research Consortium will coordinate such international challenge together with the Guglielmo Marconi University, partner of the Consortium, and in cooperation with the University of Rome Tor Vergata and the University ROMA TRE. The two-years project started on 1st, January 2021 with a budget of 350k€. The main goals of the project will be:
1. Identification of alternative wireless technologies (or alternative bearers) for communications in the railway sector (Workstream 1);
2. Study and assessment of communication protocols for railway applications (Workstream 2);
3. Dissemination of results among stakeholders, industrial partners, and within programs of the railway world such as Shif2Rail and X2Rail-5.

MMS Rail Systems Ltd provides professional engineering services for railway projects, from concept development and specification, through implementation, to assurance and entry into service.
The services offered support high speed, mainline, and metro railway systems.

With safety, integrity and respect being the values of MMS Rail Systems Ltd, as a client you can be confident that the services are delivered safely and professionally, with outputs provided on-time and to the agreed budget. Collaboration, trust and teamwork are considered to be key to success. 

Specialising in implementation strategy development, railway systems testing and commissioning, ETCS, with extensive experience in Control, Command & Signalling and Level Crossing implementation.
MMS Rail Systems Ltd provides engineering support for all phases of the system and project life-cycle.

Engineering support can be provided in the following areas:
Concept and system development;
Requirements development;
Requirements management;
Company standards and specification;
Procurement engineering support;
Tendering and estimating;
System safety and assurance; 
Systems engineering; 
System integration;
Planning and programme integration;
Project delivery;
Project engineering;
Design, manufacture, construction and installation;
Testing and commissioning, including test facilities; and 
Assurance and entry into service.

MMS Rail Systems Ltd also provide resource in the following project delivery roles:
Engineering Management;
Systems Engineering;
System Integration;
Project Engineering;
Testing & Commissioning Management;
Testing & Commissioning CRE;
Tester in Charge; and
Signalling Test Engineering duties.

MMS Rail Systems Ltd provide services in both the UK and internationally, can work independently, as part of a client team or embedded in the supply chain.
Services are provided from MMS Rail Systems Ltd office location, or co-located with the project team.

Contact: m.mcsheffrey@mmsrailsystems.co.uk

Professional Project Planning is gespecialiseerd in het plannen van projecten. Hieronder vallen de volgende activiteiten:

Het opstellen, analyseren en onderhouden van (probabilistische) netwerkplanningen voor projecten of programma’s in onder andere de bouw-, infra-, transport-, olie- en ICT-sector.

Het opstellen van resourceplanningen, capaciteitsplanningen, planningsscenario’s, voortgangs-, project- en managementrapportages, planningsdoorsnedes, afhankelijkheden tussen disciplines, projectteamleden en deelprojecten;

Het uitvoeren van risicoanalyses, what-if analyses, capaciteitsanalyses, knelpuntenanalyses, kritieke pad analyses, S-curve analyses;

Het verwerken van voortgangsinformatie,  (gewijzigde) procedures, (gewijzigde) wetgeving, de impact van issuemanagement (op tijd, geld, scope en kwaliteit), wijzigingen in risico’s, kosteninformatie, planningen van derden;

Het voeren van scope- , risico-, planning- en voortgangsinterviews;

Het monitoren en bewaken van planningen, voortgang, projectfocus, knelpunten, procedures, risico’s en issues;

Het presenteren van de (netwerk) projectplanning, rapportages, bijsturingsvoorstellen, procesverbeteringsvoorstellen;

Het adviseren t.a.v. planningsoptimalisatie, scenario’s en procesverbetering a.d.h.v. rapportages, doorsnedes en kengetallen;

Het ondersteunen in het procesmatig afhandelen van issue- en risicomanagement, het gebruik van Webaccess, de implementatie (technische en business implementatie) van Primavera, MS Project, EPM en Pertmaster, het vertalen van bedrijfsprocessen naar ICT oplossingen in Primavera, MS Project, EPM en Pertmaster.

Rail Industry Supplies is an Australian company that is dedicated to supplying quality parts to the rolling stock industry.

We provide parts predominately for companies involved in the maintenance and manufacture of wagons. RIS is first and foremost a customer focused company that prides ourselves on not only meeting but exceeding our customers needs and expectations:

We achieve this through holding large quantities of the products, routinely supplied for maintenance, on site;

Having an on site design office that can accommodate custom designs;

Working closely with our customers to deliver a tailored approach; and

Employing people with a wealth of railway experience.

Компания  «Транспортные технологии» разрабатывает и производит:

    системы управления, автоматики и телемеханики для железнодорожного транспорта, метрополитенов и промышленных предприятий;
    системы и оборудование громкоговорящей (парковой) связи и оповещения;
    системы и оборудование оперативно-технологической (командно-поисковой) и диспетчерской связи;
    оборудование защиты от коммутационных перенапряжений и грозовых разрядов;
    системы и блоки бесперебойного электропитания систем и оборудования автоматики и связи;
    корпусные изделия (распределительные и телекоммуникационные щиты, стойки и шкафы, кабельные желоба и прочие изделия).

Компания  «Транспортные технологии» инвестирует значительные средства в разработку новых технологий и видов продукции, а также осуществляет модернизацию существующих изделий в соответствии с новыми требованиями и потребностями наших клиентов. Для производства нашей продукции используется современное высокотехнологичное оборудование ведущих мировых производителей.

Предприятие располагает развитой инфраструктурой, включающей собственное производство, испытательные лаборатории и высококвалифицированный научно-технический персонал разработчиков, что позволяет обеспечить полный замкнутый цикл производства нашей продукции (от разработки до внедрения).

Собственные производственные мощности, развитая служба технической поддержки, сервисное гарантийное и послегарантийное обслуживание, внедрение на предприятии системы менеджмента качества, соответствующей стандарту ISO 9001:2008 (сертификат), высокая квалификация наших сотрудников и большой практический опыт работы позволяют нам гарантировать качество производства, высокие технические показатели и надёжность нашей продукции.
